le="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>For the last 2 days I have been posting on the FluTruxClan,  Well yesterday they came into town.  The following pictures are a short chronicle of what the Nazi scum have done to my town.

Firstly we have a some proudly wearing "Canada First" hats on Parliament Hill.  For those unaware of context "Canada First" is the adapted KKK slogan of "America First".  Yup, what we have here are Canadian members of the KKK.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/GIuWvaS.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>The Shepherds of Good Hope is Ottawa's largest soup kitchen.  They have been around for decades, help those in the community experiencing homelessness.  Yesterday they were attacked by members of the convoy who couldn't be bothered walking the 200 feet over to the shopping mall and eating in the food court.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/VB5PaNl.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Actually scratch that.  Some of the fuckers did make it to the Rideau Center, Ottawa's larges mall.   They never wore masks, tried to remove other shoppers masks, telling them "You don't need to wear that.  You're free now."

When security tried to stop them it start a physical altercation.  They started looting the mall as they were leaving.  As a security precaution the mall was shut down entirely.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/TQEV6kR.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Alberta MP Michael Cooper was handing out coffee to protestors all day.  Here he is giving a TV interview about how this rally is about freedom and unity, while standing in front of someone holding an upside down Canadian Flag that has been defaced by a swastika.  And Mr Cooper didn't seem to have any issues with it as he handed the man a cup of coffee only a few moments before.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/in4Z0yy.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>They defaced the statues of Canadian hero and icon Terry Fox.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/eQNHlOp.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>They danced on the grave of the Unknown Soldier and vandalized the War Memorial.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/UQ1DGhJ.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>(not in my city) but the Victoria BC leg of the FluTruxKlan hung effigies outside the BC Ministry of Health's building.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/RBhd6nL.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Oh yeah, AND THEY FLEW AN ACTUAL NAZI FLAG WHILE HANDING OUT ZEIG HEIL SALUTES TO THOSE WALKING BY!!!

On top of this there are several other things I don't have pictures for:

-The downtown core was entirely shut down as there was literally no more room for any vehicles or pedestrians

-The event forced the province of Quebec to shut down all interprovincial bridges

-This stopped Montfort Hospital workers who live across the river from crossing safely until the police had managed to clear a route to the hospital, putting hundreds of patients at risk because of staff shortages

-This put the lives of  every outpatient living in the downtown core at risk as their home nurses could not reach them;  we are speaking of everything from simple surgery recovery to chemo patients, many of them whose lives depend on a timely administration of medication, again putting lives at risk

Make no mistake, this convoy was never about freedom.  It has always been about hate.  The organizers have direct ties to white supremist, white nationalist, and nazi groups.  The people who showed up, reflected that.

I am furious that this scum was allowed in and out of my city without any repercussions.  This should never be allowed to happen again.

